revision.text:
'''Anne Korin''' is co-director of the [[Institute for the Analysis of Global Security]], a think tank focused on energy and security, and chairs the [[Set America Free Coalition]], an alliance of national security, environmental, labor and religious groups promoting ways to reduce America's dependence on foreign oil. She is co-author of [[Energy Security Challenges for the 21st Century]] (2009) and [[Turning Oil into Salt]] (2009). She appears in the media frequently and has written articles for [[Foreign Affairs]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foreignaffairs.org/20041101faessay83606/gal-luft-anne-korin/terrorism-goes-to-sea.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-12-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071214040613/http://www.foreignaffairs.org/20041101faessay83606/gal-luft-anne-korin/terrorism-goes-to-sea.html |archivedate=2007-12-14 |df= }}</ref> [[MIT Innovations]],<ref>http://www.iags.org/innovations_korinwoolsey08.pdf</ref> [[The American Interest]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.the-american-interest.com/article.cfm?piece%3D182 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-09-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101130052032/http://the-american-interest.com/article.cfm?piece=182 |archivedate=2010-11-30 |df= }}</ref> and [[National Review]].<ref>http://energy.nationalreview.com/post/?q=OTlmMjFjYWRjOWI3ZGI0MzUxZDJjYTBlMmUzOTc2Mzc= {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081004113613/http://energy.nationalreview.com/post/?q=OTlmMjFjYWRjOWI3ZGI0MzUxZDJjYTBlMmUzOTc2Mzc%3D |date=2008-10-04 }}</ref>

In May 2008, Korin testified before the [[House Committee on Foreign Affairs]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://foreignaffairs.house.gov/110/kor052208.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-11-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081125094005/http://foreignaffairs.house.gov/110/kor052208.htm |archivedate=2008-11-25 |df= }}</ref>

Korin is adviser to the [http://www.usesc.org United States Energy Security Council].

